  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in the bottom of a clay tagine or a heavy pot over medium heat.",
    "Chop the onion and add it to the pot, cooking until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Mince the garlic and ginger, and add them to the pot, cooking for another minute.",
    "Add the cumin, coriander, paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and black pepper, and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the ikura, olives, and apricots to the pot, and stir to combine.",
    "Reduce heat to low and simmer, uncovered, for 10-15 minutes, or until the sauce has thickened slightly.",
    "Taste and adjust seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve the tagine over couscous or pita bread, garnished with chopped fresh herbs, if desired."
